<rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News]]></title><link/> https://sputniknews.com/新闻<atom:link href="https://rsshub.app/sputniknews" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><description><![CDATA[news - Sputnik News - Made with love by RSSHub(https://github.com/DIYgod/RSSHub)]]></description><generator> RSSHub</generator><webmaster> i@diygod.me (DIY神)</webmaster><language> zh-cn</language><lastbuilddate> 2023 年 5 月 22 日星期一 03:13:04 GMT</lastbuilddate><ttl> 120 </ttl><item><title><![CDATA[Russian Ambassador Warns Against Strikes on Crimea, Raises F-16 Issue]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110508782" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110456552_0:0:2000:977_1440x900_80_0_1_d69bae7ef171fc7f43b5e273e5a04964.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1110456534" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/russian-ambassador-warns-against-strikes-on-crimea-raises-f-16-issue-1110508782.html?share-img=1110456534"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Toby Talbot</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">在这张 2001 年 12 月的档案照片中，一架 F-16 从佛蒙特州南伯灵顿的空军国民警卫队基地起飞，加力燃烧室发光，满载响尾蛇导弹。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="In this Dec. 2001 file photograph, an F-16 takes off with afterburners glowing loaded with live Sidewinder missiles from the Air National Guard base in South Burlington, Vt. - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="在这张 2001 年 12 月的档案照片中，一架 F-16 从佛蒙特州南伯灵顿的空军国民警卫队基地起飞，加力燃烧室发光，满载响尾蛇导弹。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110456552_132:0:1869:977_1920x0_80_0_0_baddefe375461e4835f816ccca217a9d.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110456552_132:0:1869:977_640x0_80_0_0_dff1a8ee0288d3203705432fcd4a1f9a.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110456552_132:0:1869:977_1280x0_80_0_0_d2342fbe5579328e15a2778f9527c8c9.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/05/13/1110456552_132:0:1869:977_1920x0_80_0_0_baddefe375461e4835f816ccca217a9d.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Toby Talbot </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据华盛顿（人造卫星）网报道：美国必须明白，乌克兰对克里米亚的袭击将被视为对俄罗斯任何其他地区的袭击，而将 F-16 战斗机转移到基辅则引发了北约卷入乌克兰冲突的问题，俄罗斯驻美国大使阿纳托利安东诺夫说。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">美国总统拜登在日本七国集团峰会上告诉乌克兰总统泽伦斯基，美国及其合作伙伴将启动一项针对乌克兰军事飞行员的培训计划，包括 F-16 在内的第四代战斗机。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我想警告政府代表不要对克里米亚做出轻率的判断，尤其是‘祝福’基辅政权对半岛发动空袭。我想提醒你们，我们认为对这片领土的袭击是对俄罗斯联邦任何其他主体的攻击。重要的是美国要充分了解俄罗斯的反应，”安东诺夫说。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">白宫国家安全顾问杰克沙利文周六表示，乌克兰拥有 F-16 的时机还不成熟，并补充说美国及其盟友将决定哪些国家将向基辅提供这些飞机以及数量。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>安东诺夫说，“每个专家都知道，在乌克兰没有运行 F-16 的基础设施，也没有所需数量的飞行员和维修人员。如果美国战斗机从北约机场起飞，由外国控制，将会发生什么？ ‘志愿者’？”</strong></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 22 May 2023 02:50:04 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/russian-ambassador-warns-against-strikes-on-crimea-raises-f-16-issue-1110508782.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/russian-ambassador-warns-against-strikes-on-crimea-raises-f-16-issue-1110508782.html<category>军队</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>阿纳托利·安东诺夫</category><category>我们</category><category>乌克兰</category><category>美乌关系</category><category>歼16</category><category>基辅</category><category>基辅</category><category>北约</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Turkiye Reportedly in Talks With West on Eliminating Obstacles to Paying for Russian Products]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110508668" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/07/1106110845_0:0:3042:2048_1440x900_80_0_1_e008404c7638336e2994f32f27dd3043.jpg?source-sid=rian_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1106110828" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/turkiye-reportedly-in-talks-with-west-on-eliminating-obstacles-to-paying-for-russian-products-1110508668.html?share-img=1106110828"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Sputnik / Vitaly Timkiv</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">俄罗斯大米</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="rian_photo" alt="Russian rice - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="俄罗斯大米" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/07/1106110845_0:169:3043:1880_1920x0_80_0_0_3f0dc9ff8b13b66bbb6b7233d4931068.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/07/1106110845_0:169:3043:1880_640x0_80_0_0_708be8c77fefd51289597cfc9e3c13b7.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/07/1106110845_0:169:3043:1880_1280x0_80_0_0_66580bc6c85306db9d1c1178cb14e5a7.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/07/1106110845_0:169:3043:1880_1920x0_80_0_0_3f0dc9ff8b13b66bbb6b7233d4931068.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © Sputnik / Vitaly Timkiv</div> / </div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据安卡拉（人造卫星）网报道：土耳其和联合国正在与美国和英国谈判，以消除支付俄罗斯产品的障碍，俄罗斯产品的出口计划作为粮食交易的一部分，消息人士熟悉会谈的人告诉人造卫星。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">本月早些时候，俄罗斯外交部表示，粮食协议已延长至 7 月 17 日，没有任何变化，但如果该倡议的所有问题未能在两个月内得到解决，该协议将在 7 月 17 日之后终止。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该部补充说，在俄罗斯-联合国备忘录的框架内有五项“系统性”任务需要解决，包括俄罗斯农业银行与 SWIFT 系统的重新连接以及俄罗斯公司资产的解冻。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text"> “目前，我们正在与联合国一起与西方国家，主要是美国和英国进行谈判，以便在俄罗斯产品进入世界市场时消除金融交易障碍。这个过程很艰难，但谈判仍在继续。”我可以说，有一种理解认为，这对于该机制的顺利运作是必要的，”消息人士告诉人造卫星网。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110508668" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/turkiye-reportedly-in-talks-with-west-on-eliminating-obstacles-to-paying-for-russian-products-1110508668.html?share-block=1110508671" data-title="&quot;Currently, together with the UN, we are negotiating with Western countries, mainly with the US and the United Kingdom, in order to remove obstacles in financial transactions when Russian products gain access to world markets. The process is difficult, but negotiations continue. I can say that there is an understanding that this is necessary for the smooth operation of the mechanism,&quot; the source told Sputnik."></div></div></div></div></div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 22 May 2023 02:36:04 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/turkiye-reportedly-in-talks-with-west-on-eliminating-obstacles-to-paying-for-russian-products-1110508668.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/turkiye-reportedly-in-talks-with-west-on-eliminating-obstacles-to-paying-for-russian-products-1110508668.html<category>俄罗斯</category><category>俄罗斯</category><category>俄罗斯之门</category><category>粮食</category><category>粮食出口</category><category>我们</category><category>英国</category><category>联合国 (UN) </category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Not Something You Budget For’: Quadruple Murder Probe Bleeding Idaho City Dry]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110508502" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/08/1106127784_0:0:3072:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_9f1e8e222a353c1deabf0d4e4e4e18fc.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1106127767" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/not-something-you-budget-for-quadruple-murder-probe-bleeding-idaho-city-dry-1110508502.html?share-img=1106127767"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Matt Rourke</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2023 年 1 月 3 日，星期二，在宾夕法尼亚州斯特劳兹堡的门罗县法院举行引渡听证会后，被控杀害四名爱达荷大学学生的布莱恩科伯格离开了。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Bryan Kohberger, who is accused of killing four University of Idaho students, leaves after an extradition hearing at the Monroe County Courthouse in Stroudsburg, Pa., Tuesday, Jan. 3, 2023. - Sputnik International, 1920, 22.05.2023" title="2023 年 1 月 3 日，星期二，在宾夕法尼亚州斯特劳兹堡的门罗县法院举行引渡听证会后，被控杀害四名爱达荷大学学生的布莱恩·科伯格离开了。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/08/1106127784_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_de3026807fda9a66be49f26e684ff5f1.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/08/1106127784_0:160:3072:1888_640x0_80_0_0_88cb07cb3911db54d791a7f3fd6b4fd9.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/08/1106127784_0:160:3072:1888_1280x0_80_0_0_77f4dccc2ae579da068b887d19f90c6b.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e7/01/08/1106127784_0:160:3072:1888_1920x0_80_0_0_de3026807fda9a66be49f26e684ff5f1.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © AP Photo / 马特·洛克</div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">悦里德</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_wyatt_reed/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">由于该市的年度警察预算已经远远超过其年度财产税收入，人们越来越担心对四名大学生的可怕谋杀案的调查可能会打破银行。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">爱达荷州莫斯科小城发生可怕的四人杀人案六个月后，警方调查杀人案的法案即将到期——当地领导人和居民都在为影响做好准备。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在爱达荷大学学生 Kaylee Goncalves、Madison Mogen、Xana Kernodle 和 Ethan Chapina 被高调谋杀后，美国一家主要媒体周日<u><a href="https://apple.news/AlILB1fSJRrOBGayI0ML3Vg">报道说</a></u>，加班费以及该市的其他费用“呈指数级增长”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">杀戮发生在一名 28 岁的犯罪学博士身上。名叫布赖恩·科伯格 (Bryan Kohberger) 的学生被指控犯有四项一级谋杀罪，但即使在对科伯格的罪行展开重大调查之前，莫斯科长期以来一直面临严重的财政短缺。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">当地官员指出，警察局的年度预算为 720 万美元，已经超过了每年带来的 690 万美元的财产税。据报道，这笔支出仅占该市年度支出的三分之一多一点。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110508502" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/not-something-you-budget-for-quadruple-murder-probe-bleeding-idaho-city-dry-1110508502.html?share-block=1110508506" data-title="Local officials noted that, with an annual $7.2 million price tag, the police department’s budget already exceeded the $6.9 million in property taxes brought in each year. The outlay reportedly comprises just over a third of the city’s yearly expenditures."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我们没有为此做好准备，”莫斯科市议会议员桑德拉凯利告诉美国媒体。 “这太可怕了——你怎么能为此做好计划？你为火灾做预算。你为洪水做预算。您为自然灾害做好准备。这不自然。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “成本是天文数字。当然，你不能在保证人员安全方面吝啬，”凯利解释道。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">但是“这不是你预算的事情，”她说，“因为这是你做梦也想不到的事情。” </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110508502" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230522/not-something-you-budget-for-quadruple-murder-probe-bleeding-idaho-city-dry-1110508502.html?share-block=1110508509" data-title="But “this is just not something you budget for,” she said, “because it's something you'd never dream could happen.&quot;"></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">她并不是唯一一位对该市财政状况表示担忧的地方政客。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>莫斯科市长 Art Bettge 告诉美国媒体，“莫斯科并没有充斥着资金过剩，”他补充说，“我们的预算非常非常精简，调查的影响已经体现在预算上。”</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Bettge 说，自去年 11 月警方发现四名学生在他们校外的房子里被刺死以来，这座城市面临着“艰难的六个月”。一个多月后，Kohberger 在他位于宾夕法尼亚州的家中因涉嫌犯罪而被捕。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">在最近对他提出起诉后，嫌疑人预计将在定于周一举行的传讯中认罪。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 22 May 2023 02:18:50 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/not-something-you-budget-for-quadruple-murder-probe-bleeding-idaho-city-dry-1110508502.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230522/not-something-you-budget-for-quadruple-murder-probe-bleeding-idaho-city-dry-1110508502.html<category>美洲</category><category>爱达荷州立大学</category><category>爱达荷大学</category><category>谋杀</category><category>谋杀调查</category><category>谋杀调查</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[‘Game Changer’ — Huge Network of Ancient Mayan Cities and Highways Could Rewrite History]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110507955" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/07/1a/1079986656_0:0:1920:1159_1440x900_80_0_1_25a6112dae6988bd458d3fa489e586b1.jpg?source-sid=cc_0" data-photoview-image-id="1079986654" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/game-changer--huge-network-of-ancient-mayan-cities-and-highways-could-rewrite-history-1110507955.html?share-img=1079986654"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright"><a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> //</span><span class="photoview__desc-text">库库尔坎古玛雅神庙</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="cc_0" alt="Ancient Mayan Temple of Kukulkan - Sputnik International, 1920, 21.05.2023" title="库库尔坎古玛雅神庙" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/07/1a/1079986656_0:40:1920:1120_1920x0_80_0_0_59793cae4f526362a44ad72dafabb93f.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/07/1a/1079986656_0:40:1920:1120_640x0_80_0_0_284600adaa2e1b311ea6f81a8a8a5580.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/07/1a/1079986656_0:40:1920:1120_1280x0_80_0_0_d10342390137d03ba05ffddafafb1d0f.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e4/07/1a/1079986656_0:40:1920:1120_1920x0_80_0_0_59793cae4f526362a44ad72dafabb93f.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> <a href="https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/" title="CC0">CC0</a> / / </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__author"><div class="article__author-item"><div class="article__author-wrapper"><div class="article__author-info"><div class="article__author-name">悦里德</div><div class="article__author-links"><a class="m-color-main" href="https://sputniknews.com/author_wyatt_reed/" title="所有材料">所有材料</a></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">长期以来，一小群土著研究人员一直在挑战玛雅人是一个相对较新的文明的观念。一项新的研究表明他们一直都是对的。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">科学家们在今天的危地马拉发现了一个由 417 个城市组成的庞大网络，其历史可以追溯到公元前 1000 年左右，这些城市由近 110 英里的“高速公路”相连，这些高速公路被称为“世界上第一个高速公路系统”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">据研究人员称，“激光雷达”技术揭示了一个具有复杂经济、社会和政治体系的高度发达文明的证据——一种相对较新的雷达，用于穿透丛林茂密的树冠和下面的任何灌木丛。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">除了巨大的道路和城市，许多仪式建筑、农业基础设施，甚至水利系统都表明中美洲古代玛雅文明远比西方学者认为的复杂得多。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110507955" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/game-changer--huge-network-of-ancient-mayan-cities-and-highways-could-rewrite-history-1110507955.html?share-block=1110508224" data-title="In addition to the massive roads and cities, a number of ceremonial buildings, agricultural infrastructure, and even hydraulic systems all suggest Central America’s ancient Mayan civilization was vastly more sophisticated than Western academics have ever given them credit for."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">该研究的主要作者理查德·汉森 (Richard Hansen) <u><a href="https://www.washingtonpost.com/science/2023/05/20/mayan-civilization-pyramid-discoveries-guatemala/">表示</a></u>，在这一突破性发现之前，大多数科学家认为，只有该地区的居民才会“游牧成群结队，种植玉米”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “我们现在知道，前古典时期是一个异常复杂和建筑精密的时期，世界历史上一些最大的建筑都是在这段时间建造的，”汉森说，他还领导着一个以玛雅为重点的非营利组织，称为人类学研究基金会和环境研究。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">汉森说，就纠正当权派偏爱的美国历史观点而言，这些发现是“游戏规则的改变者”，并补充说，他们揭开了“我们从未了解的一整卷人类历史”的面纱。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员说，来自那个时代的文物很可能被后来的玛雅建筑所掩埋，随后被哈勃增长所覆盖。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">这项<u><a href="https://www.cambridge.org/core/journals/ancient-mesoamerica/article/lidar-analyses-in-the-contiguous-miradorcalakmul-karst-basin-guatemala-an-introduction-to-new-perspectives-on-regional-early-maya-socioeconomic-and-political-organization/31075DFA8ADBAA5E7C7320CA6DB93E5E">研究</a></u>被描述为“迄今为止在玛雅低地发表的最大的、连续的、区域性激光雷达研究之一的介绍”，揭示了“超过 775 个古代玛雅定居点……以及周围的 189 个”区域，考古测试发现是从中期和晚期前古典时期。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110507955" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/game-changer--huge-network-of-ancient-mayan-cities-and-highways-could-rewrite-history-1110507955.html?share-block=1110508226" data-title="The study, described as “an introduction to one of the largest, contiguous, regional LiDAR studies published to date in the Maya Lowlands,” revealed “more than 775 ancient Maya settlements… and 189 more in the surrounding” areas, which archeological testing found to be from the Middle and Late Preclassic periods."></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">此外，该地区的“纪念性建筑、一致的建筑格式、特定的场地边界、水资源管理/收集设施和 177 公里的高架前古典堤道”表明玛雅人拥有“挑战较小政体组织能力的劳动力投资”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">研究人员说，定居点的数量和分布以及其中建筑的连续性“为特定地理区域内的早期集中管理和社会经济战略提供了证据”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>据报道，该论文的合著者圣卡洛斯大学考古学家恩里克埃尔南德斯表示，这一发现可以与埃及的金字塔相媲美，作为展示古代人类发展的精神象征 - 并且有一天可能会吸引同样多的游客。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">一家美国媒体解释说，特别重要的是“Balamnal 的图像，这是前古典文明的重要中心之一，[which] 首次公开”。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">根据主要作者汉森的说法，2009 年之前在 Balamnal 周围进行的挖掘“未能认识到这座城市令人难以置信的复杂程度和规模，所有这些都通过激光雷达技术立即显现出来。”</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">激光雷达表明该遗址是该地区最大的遗址之一，“辐射到其他较小遗址的道路表明它在前古典时期的行政、经济和政治重要性，”他指出。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 21 May 2023 23:16:16 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230521/game-changer--huge-network-of-ancient-mayan-cities-and-highways-could-rewrite-history-1110507955.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230521/game-changer--huge-network-of-ancient-mayan-cities-and-highways-could-rewrite-history-1110507955.html<category>超越政治</category><category>玛雅人</category><category>历史</category><category>古代历史</category><category>科学与技术</category><category>人类学</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Top Turkish Diplomat Slams Kilicdaroglu Over Russia Meddling Claims]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110507827" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/04/08/1082575438_0:0:2923:2047_1440x900_80_0_1_da68dac85eb6b172d315c0667409c5e4.jpg?source-sid=ap_photo" data-photoview-image-id="1082575436" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/top-turkish-diplomat-slams-kilicdaroglu-over-russia-meddling-claims-1110507827.html?share-img=1082575436"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© AP Photo / Stephanie Lecocq</span> <span class="photoview__desc-text">2021 年 1 月 21 日，星期四，土耳其外交部长梅夫卢特·恰武什奥卢 (Mevlut Cavusoglu) 与欧盟外交政策负责人何塞普·博雷尔 (Josep Borrell) 在布鲁塞尔举行会议之前发表联合声明。</span> </div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="ap_photo" alt="Turkey's Foreign Minister Mevlut Cavusoglu gives a joint statement with European Union foreign policy chief Josep Borrell prior to their meeting in Brussels, Thursday, Jan. 21, 2021. - Sputnik International, 1920, 21.05.2023" title="2021 年 1 月 21 日，星期四，土耳其外交部长梅夫鲁特·恰武什奥卢 (Mevlut Cavusoglu) 与欧盟外交政策负责人何塞普·博雷尔 (Josep Borrell) 在布鲁塞尔举行会议之前发表了联合声明。" src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/04/08/1082575438_0:202:2923:1846_1920x0_80_0_0_46fb3cd89a60a40bb8ab91a37d8aa117.jpg" decoding="async" width="1920" height="1080" srcset="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/04/08/1082575438_0:202:2923:1846_640x0_80_0_0_6c844926341aec0f3b46944280225b79.jpg 640w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/04/08/1082575438_0:202:2923:1846_1280x0_80_0_0_eae1adc5a4e1214b26ab9e96fa12b2b9.jpg 1280w,https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/07e5/04/08/1082575438_0:202:2923:1846_1920x0_80_0_0_46fb3cd89a60a40bb8ab91a37d8aa117.jpg 1920w" referrerpolicy="no-referrer"></div></div><div class="media__copyright " data-nosnippet=""><div class="media__copyright-item m-copyright"> © 美联社照片 / Stephanie Lecocq </div></div></div></div><div class="article__messengers"><div class="flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label"></span></div><div class="flex-align_center"></div><div class="article__telegram-news flex-align_center"><span class="article__google-news__label">订阅</span></div><div class="flex-align_center"><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/SputnikInt" title="国际的" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">国际的</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://telegram.me/sputniknewsindia" title="印度" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">印度</a></div><div class="article__telegram-button"><a href="https://t.me/sputnik_africa" title="非洲" class="" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">非洲</a></div></div></div><div class="article__announce-text">据安卡拉（人造卫星）网报道：土耳其外交部长梅夫鲁特·恰武什奥卢批评反对派领导人凯末尔·基利奇达罗格鲁错误地指责俄罗斯干预将于下周日决定的总统竞选。 </div></div><div class="article__body"><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> Kilicdaroglu 在第一轮投票前表示，俄罗斯正在干涉选举进程，但没有提供任何证据或细节来支持他的说法。克里姆林宫否认了这一指控。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"> “Kilicdaroglu 先生一直在威胁俄罗斯。破坏我们与这样一个国家的关系是错误的，”Cavusoglu 在接受 Haberturk 新闻频道采访时说。 </div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="quote"><div class="article__quote"><div class="article__quote-text">这位部长说，他已经问过将在 5 月 28 日的决选中挑战总统雷杰普·塔伊普·埃尔多安的 Kilicdaroglu，他是否有任何俄罗斯干预的证据，对此他的回答是“这是我的印象”。 </div><div class="article__quote-info"><div class="elem-info"><div class="elem-info__share"><div class="share" data-id="1110507827" data-url="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/top-turkish-diplomat-slams-kilicdaroglu-over-russia-meddling-claims-1110507827.html?share-block=1110507830" data-title="The minister said he had asked Kilicdaroglu, who will challenge President Recep Tayyip Erdogan in the May 28 runoff, if he had any evidence of Russian meddling, to which he responded with &quot;It was my impression.&quot; "></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text"><strong>恰武什奥卢表示，这位有抱负的总统应该“更加严肃”，不要根据自己的直觉对其他国家进行无端指责。</strong></div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">这位外交官还否认俄罗斯允许土耳其将天然气付款推迟到 2024 年的决定与选举有任何关系。 Cavusoglu 表示，在去年价格飙升后，Turkiye 正在与所有供应商协商延期支付天然气费用。</div></div><div class="article__block" data-type="text"><div class="article__text">关于叙利亚，恰武什奥卢说，土耳其正在与叙利亚政府谈判难民返回问题。他估计有 50 万叙利亚人从土耳其返回到他们祖国所谓的安全区。</div></div></div> ]]>;</description><pubDate> Sun, 21 May 2023 22:46:29 GMT</pubDate><guid ispermalink="false"> https://sputniknews.com/20230521/top-turkish-diplomat-slams-kilicdaroglu-over-russia-meddling-claims-1110507827.html</guid><link/> https://sputniknews.com/20230521/top-turkish-diplomat-slams-kilicdaroglu-over-russia-meddling-claims-1110507827.html<category>世界</category><category>2023 年土耳其总统选举</category><category>突厥耶</category><category>俄罗斯之门</category><category>俄罗斯</category></item><item><title><![CDATA[Bulgarian Protesters Throw Red Paint at EU Liaison Office in Sofia]]></title><description><![CDATA[<div class="article__header"><div class="article__announce"><div class="media" data-media-tipe="ar16x9"><div class="media__size"><div class="photoview__open" data-photoview-group="1110507708" data-photoview-src="https://cdn1.img.sputnikglobe.com/img/104495/39/1044953953_0:0:2048:1369_1440x900_80_0_1_70efa9a14d40b5fe566b2772cbe631da.jpg?source-sid=flickr" data-photoview-image-id="1044953952" data-photoview-sharelink="https://sputnikglobe.com/20230521/bulgarian-protesters-throw-red-paint-at-eu-liaison-office-in-sofia-1110507708.html?share-img=1044953952"><noindex><div class="photoview__open-info"> <span class="photoview__copyright">© Flickr / <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/farmking/3649465749/" title="亚历克斯·洛弗尔-特洛伊">Alex Lovell-Troy</a></span><span class="photoview__desc-text">保加利亚国旗</span></div></noindex><img media-type="ar16x9" data-source-sid="flickr" alt="Bulgarian flag - Sputnik International, 1920, 21.05.2023" title="保加利亚国旗" src=